abstract: The search engine company gets off to a mixed start under its new chief executive, the co-founder Larry Page.
snippet: The search engine company gets off to a mixed start under its new chief executive, the co-founder Larry Page.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — With Larry Page, Google’s co-founder and its new chief executive, now at the helm, the search advertising giant reported financial results Thursday that fell below Wall Street analysts’ expectations.

headline.main: Revenue Rises at Google but Profit Misses Forecasts, and Analysts Point to Spending
headline.print_headline: Revenue Rises at Google but Profit Misses Forecasts, and Analysts Point to Spending
